{
  "title": "Observation → observation",
  "notes": "Top-level FHIR `Observation.code` whose resolved STANDARD concept lives in the **Observation** domain routes to the OMOP `observation` table (the sibling `Observation__measurement` edge takes the rows whose domain resolves to `Measurement`). Routing is purely by the resolved concept's `domain_id` — `category` (`social-history`/`survey`) is NOT read.\n\nPipeline: stage-1 view `mapspec/views/Observation__measurement.view.json` fans out one staging row per `code.coding[]` and carries the UNION of measurement+observation value-slots into `staging.observation_coded`. Stage-2 `mapspec/etl/_resolve_observation.sql` walks each coding `system→vocabulary_id` (cm.fhir_system_to_omop_vocab) → source `vocab.concept` → `Maps to` → standard `vocab.concept` ONCE (DISTINCT ON id,std_concept_id; LOINC preferred over SNOMED in the tie-break ORDER BY), resolves value/unit alongside, then `Observation__observation.sql` filters `std_domain='Observation'` and projects the observation schema.\n\nColumn behavior exercised by this branch (all per `Observation__observation.sql`):\n- `observation_concept_id` = standard concept; `observation_source_value` = raw code (`left(src_code,50)`); `observation_source_concept_id` = SOURCE concept_id.\n- `value_as_concept_id` ← `valueCodeableConcept.coding.first()` resolved via Maps-to; on a 1→N Maps-to the value LATERAL picks the LOWEST `concept_id` (`ORDER BY vstd.concept_id LIMIT 1`). `value_source_value` ← `valueCodeableConcept.text` (`left(...,50)`).\n- `value_as_string` ← `valueString` ONLY (`left(...,60)`); a CodeableConcept answer does NOT feed it, and a plain string does NOT feed value_as_concept_id.\n- `qualifier_source_value` ← `interpretation.first().coding.first().code` verbatim (`left(...,50)`); `qualifier_concept_id` is hardcoded NULL by the current impl (resolving it is a documented follow-up).\n- `observation_type_concept_id` = 32817 (EHR), constant for every Observation-sourced row.\n- `observation_date`/`observation_datetime` from `effectiveDateTime` cast `::date`/`::timestamp` (wall-clock kept, offset dropped — NOT UTC-converted).\n- `person_id` ← subject; `visit_occurrence_id` ← encounter; `provider_id` ← performer.first() (NULL when absent).\n- Status filter: `entered-in-error`/`cancelled`/`unknown` dropped; value-presence filter requires one of value_number/value_string/value_code/value_text.\n\nNon-varying across variants (so the value/qualifier/domain diffs are crisp): one Patient (male, born 1980-01-01), one finished AMB Encounter, status `final`, single LOINC `code.coding`, no performer. The VARYING dimension is the value representation + interpretation + which LOINC's domain drives routing.\n\nAll concept_ids verified against vocab.concept in the live DB (v20260227 bundle).",
